fields.value: Replication data for: The Measurement of the Partisan Balance of State Government

dsDescriptionValue.value: This note examines problems associated with measuring the partisan balance of state government. A description of a new publicly available dataset is given, as well as of the methods used to collect these data. The results of three data analyses using different measures of state government partisan balance demonstrate that sometimes measurement error on this variable can influence substantive findings.

publicationCitation.value: Klarner, Carl. 2003. "The Measurement of the Partisan Balance of State Government." State Politics & Policy Quarterly 3(3): 309-319.
